{{Transcript list|Snowflake|My Arm}}

==Standard dialogue==
* '''Snowflake:''' Thank you for getting our herb patches to work. Now Boulder can grow goutweed for my people, and they are very happy.
* {{topt|cond=If the player lost the [[Weiss fire notes]]:|Can I have another copy of that book?}}
** '''Player:''' Can I have another copy of that book?
** '''Snowflake:''' Yes, I have another copy for you.
** {{tbox|pic=Weiss fire notes detail.png|Snowflake gives you another tatty book of Odd Mushroom's writings.}}
** '''Player:''' Thanks.
** {{tact|other}}
* {{topt|How are you two doing?}}
** '''Player:''' How are you two doing?
** '''My Arm:''' Snowflake an' My Arm very happy. Maybe new herbie patch not da only place where new life gonna be growin' soon!
** '''Snowflake:''' Let's not get ahead of ourselves, dear! But the town is thriving; my people are much happier now they are no longer terrified of Father.
** '''My Arm:''' Dem trolls likin' da goutweed too!
** '''Player:''' That's nice.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|Can you note this basalt for me?}}
** '''Player:''' Can you note my basalt for me?
** {{tcond|If the player is carrying basalt:}}
*** {{tbox|pic=Basalt detail.png|Snowflake converts your [item/items] to [a banknote/banknotes].}}
*** {{tact|end}}
** {{tcond|If the player is not carrying basalt:}}
*** '''Snowflake:''' You aren't carrying any basalt.
*** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|I'll be off.}}
** '''Player:''' I'll be off.
** '''Snowflake:''' You will always be welcome back.
** {{tact|end}}

==When using [[basalt]] on her==
* {{tbox|pic=Basalt detail.png|Snowflake converts your [item/items] to [a banknote/banknotes].}}
* {{tact|end}}

==When using [[goat dung]] on her==
* {{tbox|pic=Goat dung detail.png|No thank you, [player name], I do not need more poo in a bucket from you.}}
* {{tact|end}}

==Treasure Trails==
===Master===
My Arm does all of the talking, even though the clue requires the player to talk to Snowflake.
* '''My Arm:''' Here, solve this.
* {{tact|receives=a puzzle box}}
* {{tbox|My Arm hands you a puzzlebox!}}
* {{tact|end}}
====Talking again====
* {{tcond|If the puzzle is not solved:}}
** '''My Arm:''' That doesn't look solved to me.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{tcond|If the puzzle is solved:}}
** '''My Arm:''' Well done [player name]. Here you go.
** {{tact|receives=a [new clue/casket]}}
** {{tbox|You've been given a [new clue/casket]!}}
** {{tact|end}}
